ediums im Museum und in der Archäologie. Als er jedoch die Seiten vom Erfinder zum Nutzer der Fotografie wechselte, wurde er zum Kritiker seiner eigenen Erfindung.  aWilliam Henry Fox Talbot (1800–1877) is best known as an early inventor of photographic processes. For the first time, based on extensive new sources, this study examines Talbot's inventions in the context of his entire oeuvre. This makes possible new interpretations of his photographs, which the author views primarily as an instrument for his diverse scientific interests, and thus as part of a broader epistemic conception.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 04. Okt 2022) 4aAltertum. 4aFotografie. 4aFotografiegeschichte. 4aWilliam Henry Fox Talbot. 7aHISTORY / Ancient / General.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus DeG Package 2015 Part 1z978311076251808iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus eBook-Package 2015z978311070098508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Arts, Architecture and Design 2015z9783110438642oZDB-23-DKA08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2015z9783110439687oZDB-23-DGG0 cEPUBz97831103807980 cprintz978305006381240uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978305009547940uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783050095479423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783050095479/original  a978-3-11-070098-5  DG Plus eBook-Package 2015b2015  a978-3-11-076251-8  DG Plus DeG Package 2015 Part 1b2015  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_CL  aEBA_CL_MUAR  aEBA_CL_PLTLJSIS  aEBA_DGALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aEBA_STMALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA12STME  aPDA5EBK  aZDB-23-DGGb2015  aZDB-23-DKAb2015